Attributes applied to every icon component.

@default { "aria-hidden": true }

cssWherePseudo.description: Use CSS `:where()` pseudo selector to reduce specificity.

collections.title: Icon Collections
collections.description:
List of known icon collections name. Used to resolve collection name ambiguity.
e.g. `simple-icons-github` -> `simple-icons:github` instead of `simple:icons-github`

When not provided, will use the full Iconify collection list.

provider.title: Icon Provider
provider.description:
Provider to use for fetching icons

- `server` - Fetch icons with a server handler
- `iconify` - Fetch icons with Iconify API, purely client-side
- `none` - Do not fetch icons (use client bundle only)

`server` by default; `iconify` when `ssr: false`

Passes a string and {@linkcode replaceValue} to the `[Symbol.replace]` method on {@linkcode searchValue}. This method is expected to implement its own replacement algorithm.

When the {@linkcode searchValue} is a `RegExp`, all matches are replaced if the `g` flag is set (or only those matches at the beginning, if the `y` flag is also present). Otherwise, only the first match of {@linkcode searchValue} is replaced.

codePointAt.name: codePointAt
codePointAt.description:
Returns a nonnegative integer Number less than 1114112 (0x110000) that is the code point
value of the UTF-16 encoded code point starting at the string element at position pos in
the String resulting from converting this object to a String.
If there is no element at that position, the result is undefined.
If a valid UTF-16 surrogate pair does not begin at pos, the result is the code unit at pos.

padStart.name: padStart
padStart.description:
Pads the current string with a given string (possibly repeated) so that the resulting string reaches a given length.
The padding is applied from the start (left) of the current string.

tags.name: param
tags.text:
maxLength The length of the resulting string once the current string has been padded.
If this parameter is smaller than the current string's length, the current string will be returned as it is.

tags.name: param
tags.text:
fillString The string to pad the current string with.
If this string is too long, it will be truncated and the left-most part will be applied.
The default value for this parameter is " " (U+0020).

padEnd.name: padEnd
padEnd.description:
Pads the current string with a given string (possibly repeated) so that the resulting string reaches a given length.
The padding is applied from the end (right) of the current string.

tags.name: param
tags.text:
maxLength The length of the resulting string once the current string has been padded.
If this parameter is smaller than the current string's length, the current string will be returned as it is.

tags.name: param
tags.text:
fillString The string to pad the current string with.
If this string is too long, it will be truncated and the left-most part will be applied.
The default value for this parameter is " " (U+0020).

padStart.name: padStart
padStart.description:
Pads the current string with a given string (possibly repeated) so that the resulting string reaches a given length.
The padding is applied from the start (left) of the current string.

tags.name: param
tags.text:
maxLength The length of the resulting string once the current string has been padded.
If this parameter is smaller than the current string's length, the current string will be returned as it is.

tags.name: param
tags.text:
fillString The string to pad the current string with.
If this string is too long, it will be truncated and the left-most part will be applied.
The default value for this parameter is " " (U+0020).
